The Stingray Nebula (Hen 3-1357), the youngest known planetary nebula as of 2010, formed in Ara; the light from its formation was first observable around 1987.
Illustrations
In illustrations, Ara is usually depicted as an altar with its smoke 'rising' southward.Ian Ridpath, Star Tales.
MythologyIn ancient Greek mythology, Ara was identified as the altar, made by the Cyclops, where the gods first made offerings and formed an alliance when they were about to fight the Titans.Hyginus, Astronomica, 39, Altar
EquivalentsIn Chinese astronomy, the stars of the constellation Ara lie within The Azure Dragon of the East (????, D?ng F?ng Q?ng Lóng).{{zh icon}} AEEA (Activities of Exhibition and Education in Astronomy) ??????? 2006 ? 7 ? 1 ?
NamesakesUSS Ara (AK-136) was a United States Navy Crater class cargo ship named after the constellation.
